HEADWORD: Anorthoclase
<hw>A*nor"tho*clase</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'an</grk> priv. + <ets>orthoclase</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A feldspar closely related to orthoclase, but triclinic. It is
chiefly a silicate of sodium, potassium, and aluminium. Sp. gr., 2.57 --
2.60.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

